summary: "We are both perfectionists, and when I would ask for another take because I knew it could be better, [Jordan Vogt-Roberts]...
caption: “We are both perfectionists, and when I would ask for another take because I knew it could be better, [Jordan Vogt-Roberts] would say, ‘I think we got it,’ and I would say, 'It’s only forever.’ It became a kind of comradely slogan that was our call to arms every morning.”

reblog.comment: “We are both perfectionists, and when I would ask for another take because I knew it could be better, [Jordan Vogt-Roberts] would say, ‘I think we got it,’ and I would say, 'It’s only forever.’ It became a kind of comradely slogan that was our call to arms every morning.”

trail.content_raw: “We are both perfectionists, and when I would ask for another take because I knew it could be better, [Jordan Vogt-Roberts] would say, ‘I think we got it,’ and I would say, 'It’s only forever.’ It became a kind of comradely slogan that was our call to arms every morning.”
trail.content: “We are both perfectionists, and when I would ask for another take because I knew it could be better, [Jordan Vogt-Roberts] would say, ‘I think we got it,’ and I would say, 'It’s only forever.’ It became a kind of comradely slogan that was our call to arms every morning.”

summary: Marvel artist Andy Park releases CAPTAIN MARVEL costume concept art
title: Marvel artist Andy Park releases CAPTAIN MARVEL costume concept art
body:
Months before the first trailer was released we got to see some low-res concept art for Captain Marvel. Now Marvel’s own Director of Visual Development and Concept Artist Andy Park has released an official version of the image. Check it out below and let us know what you think in the comments below. I absolutely LOVED creating…

Marvel artist Andy Park releases CAPTAIN MARVEL costume concept art was originally published on Get Your Comic On!

Circuit Breaker Episode 109: Golden Globe Predictions, Captain Marvel, and Bond 25

Welcome to the Awards Circuit podcast titled “CIRCUIT BREAKER!,” a weekly podcast from AwardsCircuit.com featuring host Clayton Davis along with panelists Sam Coffey, Mark Johnson, Joey Magidson, Chris James, and Karen Peterson. We discuss movies, television and all the awards shows that need predicting. New episodes are released every Monday.

Find us on Twitter at @Circuit_Pod, email us at podcast@awardscircuit.com, and submit your comments and questions at the bottom of the episode.

On the agenda:

  • THIS WAS PRE-RECORDED ON 9/25 – DOUBLE PODCAST THIS WEEK!
  • Talking about the Emmy winners.
  • We’re playing “Give them an Oscar!”
  • We got a first look at “Captain Marvel” and share our thoughts.
  • NYFF screenings: “Wildlife” from Paul Dano, “Ash is Purest White,” “Non-Fiction” from Olivier Assayas, and “The Other Side of the Wind” from Orson Welles.
  • Cary Fukunaga is taking on Bond 25.  Our thoughts are shared.
  • Oscar Prediction talk that includes Best Original Screenplay.
  • First set of Golden Globe prediction talk.

summary: You can pick literally any male superhero from the last ten years to highlight the double standards that comes from telling...
body: You can pick literally any male superhero from the last ten years to highlight the double standards that comes from telling Captain Marvel to smile, yet everybody continues to use Superman, despite the fact that there was an outrage about how gloomy he was and how the biggest criticism of his movies was that he didn’t smile. At this point, you’re not even trying to hide how hypocritical you are.

reblog.comment: You can pick literally any male superhero from the last ten years to highlight the double standards that comes from telling Captain Marvel to smile, yet everybody continues to use Superman, despite the fact that there was an outrage about how gloomy he was and how the biggest criticism of his movies was that he didn’t smile. At this point, you’re not even trying to hide how hypocritical you are.

title: Januárban jön az új Captain Marvel képregény sorozat
body:
Januárban jön az új Captain Marvel képregény sorozat

Januárban jön az új Captain Marvel képregény sorozat, az író Kelly Thompson (Rogue & Gambit, Mr. & Mrs. X, West Coast Avengers, Hawkeye, Jessica Jones), a rajzoló pedig Carmen Carnero lesz.

“Úgy gondolom, hogy a karakter rendkívül fontos, talán jobban, mint eddig bármikor” – nyilatkozta Thompson.

A kreatív csapat további tagjai: Tamra Bonvillain, Sarah Brunstad és Wil Moss.
